text.tspan: Parameters in notable artificial intelligence systems
Parameters are variables in an AI system whose values are adjusted during training to establish how input data gets
transformed into the desired output; for example, the connection weights in an artificial neural network.
Note: Parameters are estimated based on published results in the AI literature and come with some uncertainty. The authors expect the
estimates to be correct within a factor of 10.
